cyclone.name: JOSE
cyclone.current_location: about 415 miles ESE of the northern Leeward Islands
cyclone.trajectory: Jose is forecast to slow, bend northwest, and then north-northwest remaining over the open Atlantic east of the Bahamas through day-5, well south-southeast of the U.S. east coast.
cyclone.expected_landfall_location: No U.S. landfall indicated in the 5-day forecast; closest approach is near or east of the northern Leeward Islands.
cyclone.hours_to_offshore: Not applicable (storm is expected to remain hundreds of miles offshore of New York during the 5-day window)

weather_observation.impacted_coast: Northern Leeward Islands and open Atlantic east of the Bahamas through day-5; U.S. east coast not in impact zone within this period.
weather_observation.wind: No tropical-storm-force winds expected at the port within the 5-day forecast window.
weather_observation.rainfall: No significant rainfall from Jose expected through day-5.
